                  <interp inst="t18310217-237-crimeloc1390" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-237-off1387 t18310217-237-crimeloc1390"></join>. I lost these trousers on the 27th of January from my door-post, but I was not at home.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-237-person2203">
                  CHARLES 
                  LEVY
               <interp inst="t18310217-237-person2203" type="surname" value="LEVY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-237-person2203" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-237-person2203" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am eleven years old. I was at home, and the trousers were at our door - a great crowd came - a man came, took down the trousers, and ran into the crowd again; I lost sight of him - I saw the prisoner at the office on Saturday, and I know he is the man who took them - I am quite sure he is the person; I ran, and called Stop thief! but he got into the crowd - I saw his face.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-237-person2204">
                  SAMUEL 
                  WAKELING
               <interp inst="t18310217-237-person2204" type="surname" value="WAKELING"></interp>
